# Error Handling

- Use AppError: .networkError, .httpError(code:), .decodingError, .authError, .unknown
- Map at data boundary with ErrorToAppErrorMapper
- Expose error: AppError? in ViewModel and clearError() for dismissal
- Bind SwiftUI .alert(isPresented:presenting:) to error
- Treat as retryable: NetworkError, 5xx, DecodingError; treat as fatal: AuthError, 4xx
